JOHANNESBURG - The ANC has some serious business to attend to, but that isn't stopping leaders from breaking out their dance moves, to celebrate the party's 106th birthday. Senior ANC leaders kicked off 2018 in their dancing shoes. The party celebrated its 106th birthday, under the leadership of Cyril Ramaphosa. Supra Mahumapelo, Lindiwe Sisulu and Naledi Pandor proved they're young at heart. The birthday bash was held in East London. eNCA